content: My Google Play account name has changed, and now it doesn't recognize my Pro purchase, and won't let me re-purchase it again either.  I click on the "Upgrade to Pro" button and the splash screen comes up that gives me a summary of the Pro features with two buttons available, one that says "Later" and another button that says "Continue".  If I click the "Continue" button, nothing happens.  It makes the click sound and highlights monetarily, but does nothing.  The summary screen with the two buttons remains.  If I click "Later", the screen closes.  It appears that the mechanism for verifying purchases has a bug that can't handle a Google Account name change.  My original purchase of eDrawings was on September 10, 2015, and subsequently upgraded to eDrawings Pro on September 15, 2015.  On September 18, 2015, my Google Play account name changed.  Except for 3 days after initial purchase, I haven't been able to use the Pro features of the app, and I really, really need to access them now.  I opened a help case in 2015 and got a auto-reply email with a case number saying that I would be contacted, but never heard anything again.
replyContent:
Hi James,

Thank you for alerting us of this issue with such a detailed description. We will begin investigating this issue immediately using the information you have provided.

Regards,
eDrawings Support Team

content: Doesn't work on this device

Great for viewing old drawings produced on SolidWorks 2014, however after upgrading to the latest version of SolidWorks the app doesn't seem to support files produced from it. Very disappointing, especially as I work in a paper-less environment and use my tablet to view drawings while I work.
I bought pro and can't load any files into it to view. (And the files I'm trying to view were made in Edrawings). Would love any contact for resolution since I've just wasted 10.99
I need too measure with this app and it don't let me upgrade to get pro

Very buggy program that does not appear to be updated any more.  SolidWorks seems to be relying on the fact that they have the only app for viewing.  In spite of the marketing blurbs, you cannot open part or assembly files from Google Drive or email without first downloading the file and then moving it into the only directory eDrawings recognizes.  Once you do get it open, be prepared for random crashes.  If there were other options available, I recommended not wasting your time with this program.  Certainly don't waste your money on the paid pro "upgrade".

opens files (tried only small), seemed promising, bought pro. will get a refund. when measuring it is just IMPOSSIBLE to pick a second point,  there is no dead zone for picking (especially when zoomed in which sucks anyway) and rotate kicks in as you try to select. i am really curious what these guys where thinking when developing this app or if anybody has ever bothered to test its functions. configurations not appearing at all, same with exploded views. disgrace. ridiculous even if it was free.

Update:  A year ago we gave up in this app, to assist quick referencing of Assemblies on our production floor.  Just tried it again,  and it works great now. Using Android 6.0.1 on One Plus A3000  Jail Break.  Will check soon for use on iPad with latest IOS.  as of 2/11/2017

Trying to open Parts and Assemblies made with SW 2017 and they open blank, the model appears on the thumbnail but the space is completely empty (grey) when I open them, the samples seem to work just fine, love the AR function and how easy it is to setup, have to check it with cardboard when it starts working.
Good app But i have small issue.. I can't upgrade my app in edrawings pro  When i click on upgrade option it will show me unfortunately stopped.. Please solve it. Thanks.

Can not buy or install pro. only need it to check a dimension. would not reccomend application.
Doesnt allow me to upgrade to pro, even though i've bought it. No customer support.

We use Solidworks quite often for work, having the ability to carry an assembly around on a tablet would be a lifesaver, as well as help our efforts in saving paper.  However, after purchasing the app, as well as the Pro offered in the app, I cannot import our models into the app, because the 2 options, "from email, and through a cloud service" are grayed out.  Having played with the samples loaded in the app, I do find it to be a great piece of software, but I can only give 3 stars for now, as the primary function of importing OUR models in.

I have a 32Mbyte file which I was keen to view with this app. Paid to upgrade to Pro so I had measurements too, only to find the app stops working once the model has loaded. No movement no pan, rotate....Nothing.

Cannot get this to work. Saved files in a dozen filetypes including .sldprt, when I open them the screen is just blank.   Also paid extra for the Pro version.  Credit card was charged, yet app still is asking me to upgrade to pro...

When I try to open my files both the email and cloud options are grayed out.  I am sure I am missing something but the UI should make opening a file completely obvious.  I don't have the patience to figure this out.  If someone wants to explain what is wrong to me I will buy this app again.

Why SW view controls have to be so unintuitive ? 1 finger to pan, two to rotate and zoom, please get that... But 3 stars because this is the only 3D CAD files viewer that actually works on Google play...
Why so hard to get drawings and models imported....thanks to Anthony Brobson for the Dropbox clue.  It works great.  But why oh why can't it be done direct from edrawings????
Pay for this app,  then have to pay again to get the pro version.

content: 8/23/2016 Doesnt open .edrw files.
Could only open drawings from solidworks and when I asked for help they email me(5 days after asking) that i had a old version(I just downloaded the app)

I'm giving this app one more star because they added AR to Android.   However, this app is still far too buggy. It still crashes a lot. Especially when using the PRO features ironically. Section, measure and comment crash it a lot.   Also it seems that there is a limit to what size files it can even open. Large files seem to either crash or not even open.  If you want a way to show 3D designs, rotate them, explode them, (the basics) and you don't mind some crashes this app can work.  But if you are looking for a stable production tool I don't think this app is going to work. I tell people to use the PC version if they want to make comments, measure, etc.   Hopefully the app will continue to improve and become stable. Very cool program

I paid for it and does not work!

I already paid once for this, and now they want me to pay AGAIN for the 'pro' version which has features which should have been in the initial version.    And this app sets itself as the default app for many different file types which it can't even read. Fix it!

I don;t understand the lack of AR  and the lack of a reason why ?  Crap I see that I did already buy it  :-(    my fault for not reading the description, AR works great on my iPad, unfortunately I leave that at home.
I have been waiting for an app like this for a long time.
My files crash the app. Samples crash the app. Galaxy s4.  Works ok for small parts and I use it for reference but is to slow for showing other people.
Keeps crashing on Note 10.1 2014
Paid app that requires additional payments
Bought this to try AR function for work. Seems you've not allowed for a large proportion of society that doesn't use an Apple comms device... Waste of money.
Crashes when I open my files.

Love  it.

More stars when we get AR, if it is at least as good as the ipad version. It is an unreasonable omission!   This runs smoothly on a Note 2014, but that isn't surprising given it is currently one of the most powerful android tablets available. I have had a few crashes but it is mostly stable.   It isn't very expensive but the basic version is really very limited in what it can do, and frankly should be free like the desktop version.
It has never crash on me yet. Just works as advertised! I am using latest nexus 7

Please in the name of all things fix this app from open all unknown file formats. Doesnt matter which type im trying to open, by default im getting it open by edrawing. Php file,  for example from dropbox or google drive. I purchased this app so i think i may ask for that much. I already uninstalled it once because of this problem. Im not getting a fix and now you want more money from me. Why should I pay if you dont even listen?? I think I just drop this app to trash.
with few enhancements like cut sections & measurements this will be the Best. I purchased pro but measure functionability is not working.

The main functionality of this application is there, same as the desktop version. However, leaving out Augmented Reality for everyone but IPhone users is downright ignorant. Give every version of the app the same functionality or just don't do it in the first place. I originally purchased this because AR would be Incredibly helpful to communicate with customers. Nope. Can't do it. And I'm not about to switch to an OS I despise just for one feature. Application will stay uninstalled until it's added.
doesn't work on venue7 from dell. I can only open the sample files no other options? how about an OPEN FILE button?  seems pretty basic function that's missing
Works well on ss s4 mobile. But ss tab3 10.1 not so good. Just upgraded to android 4.2.2 and it works geat.
Can't get a single file to open on this app. Want my money back
All around good!
We design and fabricate automated machines and this app is what i need to show our potential customers what we can build for them.
Only for professional.

F....king robbers. I paid ¬£5 for this f....king app now Devs release pro versions and want us to pay again.....tomorrow there will be the super pro one and you loose your money again. Well done solid works. Well done.
As others have reported, access to cloud files or email is greyed out (even on the $8 version). Otherwise works pretty well, good start.

The license agreement has multiple sections which refer to Apple, rather than Google or any Android manufacturer. How do you expect users to read the terms and conditions if you can't even properly update them when porting to a new operating system?

I just paid $2.99 for the initial app and when selecting "MY FILES",  it asked to OPEN EMAIL attachments or OPEN from CLOUD. BOTH these options are disabled.  Disappointing product that has obviously not been tested.  Lucky I did not pay for the pro version as I suspect that would have been full of bugs too!!  I have a SONY Xperia C6903 Android 4.2.2
Works well, but the lack of ar is a pain. Were having to buy a load of iPad airs now to demo to our clients.

Paid the 2.99 For the app and then paid the extra 8 dollars for the pro and then tried to open a model.  Screen goes black and flickers the image on and off.    Emailed support and they told me there was a known issue with the galaxy tab 3's.  They suggested I download HoopsViewer but cant seem to open solidworks files without converting.  Dissapointed.
I paid for the app and the in app upgrade, only to find that when I open an assembly or part the screen goes black and skips between the part and a black screen when moving. Very disappointing.
I just can open the samples, every time I try to open other files the programcrashes
Great app. I would like to notice a possible fix. When a drawing is opened, and you pull the same but updated drawing from Dropbox the app will crash.
Not smooth, app crashes whn loading models. And would still prompted to upgrade to pro.
This is great to finally have on android!

I had been to a course in which the tutor demonstrated the AR features. I was very impressed and was very much looking forward to using it on my Samsung Galaxy Tab 3 8.0". But I was very disappointed to find the Android does not have AR functionality. Cost nearly ‚Ç¨9!  I can only hope that the developers are working on this.  Good app otherwise.

Basic functionality, and the augmented reality function present in ios is missing which would have been very useful for us. This is nothing difficult to do, and you've had plenty of time to get a decent Android version out. We don't pay the high costs of your desktop software just for you to support Apple devices with the  'bells and whistles'. No AR, no upgrade!
I finally can get out my phone or tablet to show complete assemblies that rotate and zoom instead of showing pictures of the preview window render. I hope it keeps getting better.
Nice, the basic features are there, hope more are on their way. Update - sorry, what? You want more money??!

Pay, and then pay some more? Bit rich asking someone to pay $3 for an app and then another $9(!) for features that are free on the desktop. Especially given most users have dropped $14+k on Solidworks.
As written below, pay for solidworks, pay for that poor app without many functions....really not satisfied with that.

**Edit: I had this app at two Stars but I am now dropping it to one. I don't want it on the list for every "open with" screen. Very annoying.
Come on guys, that's weak.  At least find a way to let customers dishing thousands of dollars per year on Solidworks maintenance to get the pro version.
Stupid thing to do
So we pay for an app and then you update it and expect payments for future updates. This is a mobile viewer. What a bunch of s**t
We put paid options into your paid app so you can pay while you pay. Pathetic.

pathetic..now we have to fork over another $8 to get what should have been!?!?..sad...classic solidworks beta...limited / basic functions... we need to hide, show, transparent, section, measure, .. open individual prts...non shaded/shaded.. notes,... decals do not display properly...and conflicts with other apps... Oct 23 same problems... hey SW Corp.. pay your developers!

The app wont allow me to import or open ANY files. When i contacted support and explained everything including OS platform and device i received an email back explaining how to use the Ipad app on Apple???????????? How stupid can your support staff be?   Be warned this app doesn't work on 4.3 or Xperia Z tablets

What a disappointment! For the most numerous mobile platform to wait for so long for this app to come and then find it to be a poor relation to that already on the iPad, is just incredible. Do Solidworks actually know what they are doing? Do they have ANY credible programmers?  There is so much missing in this app:  No Pro version is just the start, so no 'advanced' features at all;  No means to find and open files from a navigation window. And you still have to pay for the privilege!  So, will this get updated anytime soon? It really needs that to happen quickly for it to be of much use to serious Solidworks users. But knowing how slow Swks is to deal with any issues for the last years, I wouldn't hold my breath!

No file open feature, which sucks.  Still requires a ton of work to make it as useful as edrawings. I was hoping this would be cool enough to browse a local network and display files on the shop floor, but this is not possible
Useless since the import button is grayed out.  There is no way to open my own files.

Needs a working file explorer. If I put files on my android device I need to use a file explorer to find them and click them to open the app. Can't get to files inside the app... This needs a way to measure components. Also, if there is a period in the part name, say "part v1.3.sldasm" it asks what to open it with. If you select edrawings it can't open it.
Thanks for fixing the file associations problems.
Causes frequent reboots of my Note II.  Colors don't come through correctly for assemblies with several color configurations. Lacks iOS augmented reality features. I want my money back!

Pan, zoom and rotate work great and intuitively on my Nexus 10. It is very limited for assemblies though. I can't see part names in an assembly or hide parts/make transparent. You can not section the assembly either.
Great app for a great Software!
Great I can view the files. This is something I have been waiting for for a while. The one thing that would make my life easier is the ability to take a look at component's properties.

Works well on modern hardware. One major issue is that it installs as a file handler for file types. So every file you open from now on will ask if you want to open in edrawings, which is clearly a bug.
Nice viewer. edrawings defaults conflict with other apps. edrawing icon appears on birthday and relationship section in my contact widgets, as if edrawings was the default app to open those fields.
The app is what it should be however the auto association to any file type makes it unusable. Will be a good viewer once it is fixed.

userName: The Berthold Family Travel and Adventure
content: Even after trying to change the defaults back to the original programs, keeps wanting to use edrawings. Really sucks.
Cool app but it is not very useful without a measure tool.
Does a good job for its use. But it opens on every file, sound, pdf it's ridiculous!
App is nice except it tries to become the default app for everything on your phone.

The basic functionality of this app works well.  I haven't had any problems with crashing, etc. while viewing the basic SolidWorks file types.  There is much lacking in the ability to open other file types and to bring it up to speed with the iOS version of the same app.  One very major flaw is file association.  There is no file association for this app and so it tries to open anything and everything you already have on your device or that you try to download and it doesn't remember your type selections.

At last!  Edrawings for my tablet!  I can finally ditch the laptop for good in favor of using my Xoom wherever I go.    Worth paying the money if you're serious about viewing 3D cad files - and definitely worth it to me as I don't have to cart 5kg of laptop kit with me to customers now.    A few reviewers have missed functionallity that is in there - such as isolating parts to view separately (touch and hold for sub menu) etc - so a little unfair.  Works very smooth on my HTC One X .  Thank you Dassault for finally satisfying the engineers in this world (Android users) as well as the marketing suits (Apple users) - Long overdue release and very welcome.
Finally a great way to visualize parts, drawings and assemblies from solidworks. But the software crashes when trying to open Gmail messages and sometimes it restart or power off the phone.
Can't measure.    Very slow on assemblies.  Needs lots of work.    First ever app I've paid for and I wish I didn't.     PLEASE UPDATE!!!
Trys to open just about every kind of file which is annoying.  Works well at what its supposed to do, just don't take over my other functions please
Disappointing that there is no sectioning tool, visibility of components can not be controlled and individual parts can not be opened as in the PC version. OK if all you need is a viewer.

If I attempt to open a PDF link from my Chrome browser this app automatically opens and the PDF cannot be viewed. I tried resetting my app defaults with no success. I had to disable eDrawings to download the PDF. After disabling eDrawings I was then able to select which app to open my PDF in. DSS you have been working on this app for about a year, the quality of this app is quite disappointing.  T-Mo, HTC One.

With the computing power of phones today I was anxious for the day that I would be able to bring  files with me to the field on my phone to do quick measurement verifications, solidworks. That part of its great, but it tries to be the default app for everything I open, most of which is not a cad file(text messages, pdfs, word documents, etc) and I'm uninstalling this until that is fixed.

On installation edrawings appears as option to complete action for most things. This is an annoying bug. Other than this the currently limited functions are okay as a start. Please address the issue that it tries to be an option for completing pretty much all actions!

Want the AR that comes with the "pro' version not yet available on android. Will definitely upgrade to that when its available . C'mon 3Ds team. good work though. Great for showing designs when I'm on the go using my Nexus 7 or LGOG.

Opens even my larger SolidWorks files on my Nexus 7 without a problem, but please fix the intents! This app should not offer itself up for every file type, Gmail messages, and other items. Beyond that annoyance, happy with it so far.

Whenever I open email attachments (.pdfs, .docs, etc) edrawings attempts to import and prevents me from viewing them. I unistalled the app until this is fixed. It's a shame because the app works great for viewing models. Please Fix!
The app works well, with no crashes. It starts up fast when opening correct files, but it's annoying that the app shows up as a download option for ANY file extentions.

Its a good app for now to show off my models. But ever since installing it, it constantly defaults as the main app for everyfile I download. Have to manually save links so it wouldnt attempt to open in this app for eg. Powerpoints and word docs. Also you could integrate some sorta of file access to the app like dropbox or internal drive so we dont have to manually do it.

Great app. I've been waiting for this and you hit a home run. Now I can bring 3d to my customers! Measure tool will be great. How about some sort of way to draw on top of the tablet. Then you could get the modeling position and write something on it as an illustration!
Good stuff

It functions OK on my galaxy s4 but sometimes it crashes. It runs pretty slow and choppy when you scroll or zoom too. It doesn't work well at all on my next book tablet. Screen turns 90% dark when I try to do anything other than the home view. It runs android 4.1.1 though so maybe it has something to do with that.
Annoyingly puts drawings as a action or program to do all most all tasks on phone. Worked ok for SW models, but got tired of it trying to do all.

It's been an aweful long time coming but this app will be very useful.  I've given it a bit of a test run on my Google Nexus 7 and the usability and functionality is great. If only it could view STL files I would be even more impressed.

What's there seems to work ok, though I haven't tested this hard yet. Currently would be much more useful with the addition of Measure Tool and Cross Sections... possibly also Comments and Feature tree. This could be in a "Pro" version for a bit more money. Already noticed a strange bug (same as Adam Dixon) - when clicking on an Android email notification, and then selecting Gmail / Always - it reboots the phone. The second time round it's ok. Bit odd. why on earth would eDrawings want to open emails anyway?
finally for android !!!

Nice app to have on Android but needs finishing before charging for it. Should be able to open files from a file manager not just email.  Loads of weird things now try to open with Edrawings for some reason like email, tasks, maps
Great job. Works smoothly.
The fact that I had to buy this just to view files is a load of crap, but it does do its job
Great application..took time to Launce..

Cannot hide or make transparent multiple bodies.  Mostly just standard views, zoom, rotate and the PLAY button, but you can pinch to zoom while rotating, which can be nice and a pain at the same time (hard to stay normal to a normal view while zooming because of this).  Also, nearly every app is asking me whether it should be opened with eDrawings now (Open ColorNote with eDrawings?  Really???).  When opening a Gmail notification, it makes you choose between eDrawings and Gmail.  If you select Gmail and "Just Once," then it will do it correctly that one time.  If you select Gmail and "Always," it will hang your phone and then cause it to reboot - every time.  You really wouldn't think it would be that hard to solve these issues, would you?  Install this if you want to go through most of your apps and have to re-associate them with their rightful program while hitting "Always" (the other apps don't crash the phone when doing this, but who wants to go through these steps?).  Or, don't install and wait until the bugs are worked out.  I have a Samsung Galaxy Note 2.
I have to remove app completely on my 10.1 because whenever I have it on my 10.1, the app defaults to try and open every kind of file.

Great addition to solid works package. Works perfectly and smoothly on nexus 7. Could be improved with the addition of section views (instead of manual section cuts via configs) and markup options. Brilliant start though!

Great. Was waiting for this for more than a year. Would like to use it to its maximum. Markup & measure tools required. This app will be used  mostly by people reviewing designs created by other design engineers. Therefore commenting & measuring is a must. Anyway Gr8 work .
Tried to open gmail and other programs on my phone after clicking on a message.   It crashed both times.

Great app. About time. Only gripe is that I'd  like to be able to open files from other locations other than My files directly from eDrawings rather than having to select them from a File explorer app.  Apart from that, I love it.
More development required, may be pro, needs like measure comments etc.

Viewing complex assemblies is smooth, which is very good but at the moment it's only a viewer, the explode function doesn't work. It needs to have measurement functionality and the tree with parts list would be useful. The main problems are it opens instead of a pdf viewer, it's also disrupting other apps and systems, including the contacts. Due to these errors it is being uninstalled which is a shame as it has the potential to be a 5 star rating. Please fix the errors swiftly.
Would like to see background changeability and ability to recognise files uploaded to the device via USB
Easy to spin and zoom.  Can hide parts or make transparent.   Import not working on Xoom.   Should allow opening of local files, not just email and cloud.   Also needs measuring tool.
start
App works seamlessly with cloud drives and the explode feature is super handy. A must have one for product designers and project managers...
Works well and faster than I thought it would be on phone. Great tool for reviewing designs with clients.
for sure!  Still needs some work, pro features, code optimization to get better speed on large assemblies, but I see the possibilities...
Been waiting for this for forever!!! Would like to see the measure and augmented reality tools

Looks like a pretty nice app. It opens the files straight from Dropbox, which is great. But I've noticed that I can't see different configurations when using assembly files. It would be nice if I could.   Also, I think I found a bug. When I receive an email from my notifications section it asks if I would like to open the email in E-Drawings or Gmail. Once I choose Gmail my phone restarts. Maybe I'm alone?
Wish it had AR, maybe with the next update I hope. No issues as of right now.

So far I like everything about the app. Except how text is shown on drawings, can you please double check the coding for how text is shown on drawings. ¬†When I opened the sample drawing file, on my Samsung Galaxy Note II, all of the dimensions and view text was overlapping making it hard to read.

Installed on Nexus 7 and Xperia Z phone.  Great stuff. Good performance on the Nexus, but it is blown out of the water by the Xperia. Screen resolution gives an incredibly sharp image.  I now want to see the Pro tools that are on the apple version.  AR for sure.  Markups as well.
Works and looks great.
